definition: to present to a superior/memorial/petition/to present (a certain appearance)/to assume (a shape)/to be (a certain color)
to hand over/to pass on sth/to gradually increase or decrease/progressively

sentences.english: The job attributed to basophils that has spurred the most discussion is presenting antigens.
sentences.chinese: 嗜碱性细胞抗原呈递的新功能激起了最为热烈的讨论。

sentences.english: I filed my resignation with the department.
sentences.chinese: 我向系里呈递了辞职书。

sentences.english: Prepare and submit drawing to the URA for change of existing use.
sentences.chinese: 改变使用店餐厅时向市建局呈递表格。

sentences.english: The new ambassador is expected to present his credentials tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 这位新任大使预定于明日呈递国书。

sentences.english: We surrendered a clean on board bill of lading for negotiation of payment.
sentences.chinese: 议付时我们呈递了清洁装运提单。

sentences.english: I am submitting a further list to the King tonight.
sentences.chinese: 今晚我会向国王呈递一份更详细的名单。

sentences.english: If you do not have a back - up copy , you must submit a new application.
sentences.chinese: 若没有备存文档，则须呈递一份新申请。

sentences.english: The partition of silver in ores shows grading with level.
sentences.chinese: 矿石中银的配分随着标高变化呈递变现象。

sentences.english: The opinion book from the vassal to a lord.
sentences.chinese: 臣子向帝王呈递的意见书。

sentences.english: The Foreign Secretary presented his credentials to the king.
sentences.chinese: 那位外交大臣向国王呈递了国书。

sentences.english: She has lodged a complaint with the police.
sentences.chinese: 她已经向警察局呈递了诉状。

definition: memorial to the emperor (folded in accordion form)
official communication (between gov. offices of equal rank)/report delivered by the head of gov. on affairs of state
credentials (of a diplomat)/documents exchanged between nations/national or dynastic history book
